THE health department has launched an investigation into a hospital administration block gutted by fire. The incident happened at about 3am on Saturday at Themba Hospital in Kabokweni, Mpumalanga. Provincial health spokesman Dumisane Malamule said a preliminary investigation revealed a petrol bomb was thrown through a window. Furniture, computers and some records were destroyed. “The matter has been reported to the police. The department also instituted an internal investigation to get to the bottom of the incident. “The outcome of the investigation will guide us on the course of action.” According to an insider, there are internal squabbles at the hospital over positions. He alleged a supervisor was setting up some of his colleagues for failure. Police spokesman Colonel Mtsholi Bhembe told Daily Sun they were not aware of the matter and are still waiting for more information.